wikipedia_page.main: John Benjamin Keane was an Irish architect of the 19th century. (d.1859). He was engineer on the River Suir navigation.

response: A large estate house in the area, Stradone House, was built between 1828 and 1835 by architect John Benjamin Keane for the landowning Burrows family. While this burned down in 1921, during the Irish War of Independence and was subsequently demolished, a number of surrounding buildings (including stables and a gate lodge) remain.
